name: Salamone Christ
description:
The Salamone Christ is a monumental building built by the Italian-Argentine architect Francesco Salamone in Laprida, a small town without buildings. 
The entrance to this cemetery is crazy because it contrasts with the place where it was created. After the "Redentor" in Rio de Janeiro this is the tallest christ in South America.
My first NFT in HEN is a tribute to the town where I was born and its influence on me.  
Three photos on 30 meters of Christ. 1936. Buenos Aires, Argentina.
